{"source_key":"sha256-ea08d35f42d5530fbe92c80d4f5b27e9","record_index":361,"record_hash":"sha256:b502cf2b9bffcc06ea664f0718d0d58d10daf815894e2c45a16291379b896dd2","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:35:07.880Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: agent-trail.md\n@@\n-Good package shape:\n+Put the native package in the GitButler repository, next to `but-agentlog`, not\n+inside Forge. That keeps the Rust dependency graph and storage interpretation\n+with the code that owns it. Forge should consume the generated npm package.\n+\n+Good GitButler-side package shape:\n \n ```text\n-crates/agent-trail-napi or crates/but-agenttrail-napi\n-packages/agent-trail-sdk or packages/but-agenttrail-sdk\n+crates/but-agenttrail-napi\n+packages/but-agenttrail-sdk\n ```\n \n The native package should expose one small server-only function first:\n \n ```text\n-projectAgentTrail(request) -> AgentTrailProjection\n+projectAgentTrail(request: AgentTrailProjectionRequest) -> AgentTrailProjection\n ```\n \n The request should contain the prepared repo path or GitMeta source, resolved\n metadata OID, PR facts, limits, and projection version. The response should be\n@@\n artifact workflow, not reuse of the entire `but-api` surface.\n \n+Minimum implementation shape:\n+\n+```text\n+gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog\n+  src/agent_trail.rs            # public projection API and DTOs\n+\n+gitbutler/crates/but-agenttrail-napi\n+  Cargo.toml                    # cdylib, depends on but-agentlog + napi-rs\n+  build.rs                      # napi_build::setup()\n+  src/lib.rs                    # #[napi] project_agent_trail(...)\n+\n[REDACTED:entropy]\n+  package.json                  # @napi-rs/cli build scripts\n+  src/generated/index.js\n+  src/generated/index.d.ts\n+  src/generated/*.node\n+```\n+\n+The generated npm package should be server-only. It should not ship browser\n+behavior beyond a stub that throws clearly if imported client-side.\n+\n+Initial package scripts can mirror `packages/but-sdk`:\n+\n+```json\n+{\n+  \"scripts\": {\n+    \"build:napi\": \"napi build --platform --esm --manifest-path ../../crates/but-agenttrail-napi/Cargo.toml --js index.js --dts index.d.ts --output-dir ./src/generated/.\",\n+    \"build:napi:release\": \"napi build --platform --release --esm --manifest-path ../../crates/but-agenttrail-napi/Cargo.toml --js index.js --dts index.d.ts --output-dir ./src/generated/.\",\n+    \"check\": \"tsc -p tsconfig.generated.json --noEmit\"\n+  },\n+  \"napi\": {\n+    \"binaryName\": \"gitbutler-agenttrail\",\n+    \"targets\": [\n+      \"x86_64-apple-darwin\",\n+      \"aarch64-apple-darwin\",\n+      \"x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\"\n+    ]\n+  }\n+}\n+```\n+\n+Add Windows only if there is a real Forge deployment or developer need for it.\n+Linux musl should be an explicit decision, not accidental scope.\n+\n+The first Rust NAPI wrapper can be intentionally boring:\n+\n+```rust\n+#[napi]\n+pub async fn project_agent_trail(\n+    request: serde_json::Value,\n+) -> napi::Result<serde_json::Value>\n+```\n+\n+That keeps the NAPI boundary stable while the projection DTOs are still moving.\n+Once the projection settles, replace raw `serde_json::Value` with generated\n+typed DTOs or a schema-driven `.d.ts` append step like `but-ts`.\n+\n+The request should include:\n+\n+- `repoPath` or a future explicit GitMeta source handle\n+- `metadataOid`\n+- `pr`: forge host, GitHub repo id, owner, repo, PR number, base ref, head ref,\n+  and head SHA\n+- `limits`: max sessions, turns, records, bytes per record, total bytes, and\n+  runtime deadline\n+- `projectionVersion`\n+\n+The response should include only the public projection and status/warning\n+fields. It must not include raw session keys, raw turn keys, provider session\n+ids, filesystem paths, `source_record`, or hidden/system/developer messages.\n+\n+Forge consumption should stay behind a server-only TypeScript module:\n+\n+```text\n+lib/agent-trail/native.ts       # imports @gitbutler/but-agenttrail-sdk\n+lib/agent-trail/service.ts      # GitHub lookup, cache, fetch, snapshot flow\n+app/api/agent-trail/...         # JSON API route\n+app/[owner]/[repo]/pull/[number] # page over the API/projection\n+```\n+\n+All routes that touch the native package should set `runtime = 'nodejs'` and\n+must not be imported by client components. If Next's bundler tries to package\n+the native module incorrectly, configure the SDK as a server-side external\n+package in Forge rather than importing generated `.node` artifacts directly.\n+\n The helper-binary fallback remains valid when deployment constraints make NAPI\n awkward:\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:35:07.880Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}